title: For Sale:  Whinchester Model 1200 12 Gauge Shotgun.
location: North of Scobey, MT, Montana, United States
postcontent:
Whinchester Model 1200 12 Gauge Shotgun.  
Like new condition.
This is the hunting version of the Model 1200 with the longer barrel.

The Model 1200 is the original heavier build model
 that latter was produced as the lighter, cheaper Model 1300.

It was used by US Marines and US Army soldiers in Vietnam, as a supplement to the Ithaca Model 37s and Remington 870s. 
It was a successful design and was also adopted in a police riot model for many departments across the United States. 
Though the shotgun was well received, Winchester wanted to develop a 'cheaper' shotgun...(Model 1300).

This shotgun has been used perhaps fewer than 20 times.  It was treated with silicone spray.  And has been in storage many years.  And now appears to be in pristine, new, unused condition.

Location is south central Saskatchewan.


Accepting offers at setobe@yahoo.com

http://www.imfdb.org/wiki/File:Winchester1200Police.jpg

title: For Sale:  Colt Series 90 Double Eagle MK II Stainless 45 ACP
postcontent:
LSB#: 110608RP2 

Make: Colt 

Model: Double Eagle 

Serial Number: DA21857 

Year of Manufacture: 1990's 

Caliber: .45 ACP 

Action Type: Double Action / Single Action Semi Auto Pistol 

Markings: The left side of the slide is marked "Colt Double Eagle / - MK II / Series 90 -". The right side of the slide is marked "Colt Double Action". The right side of the frame is marked "Colt's Pt. FA., Mfg. Co. / Hartford, Ct. U.S.A. / DA21857". The left trigger guard shows the proof mark and a "2". The right side of the trigger guard shows a "1". 

Barrel Length: 5" 

Sights / Optics: The gun is mounted with a 3-dot sight system. The front sight is a single dot and is fixed. The rear 2-dot sight is set in a dovetail. 

Stock Configuration & Condition: The stock(s) is/are checkered plastic. The checkering is sharp, but there is wear to the checkering on the left panel and a heavier wear mark on the right panel behind the bottom screw 

Type of Finish: Stainless 

Finish Originality: Factory Original 

Bore Condition: The rifling is sharp and bright with just a bit of fowling in the grooves at the breech. There is no erosion. 

Overall Condition: This gun retains about 90% of its metal finish. The balance of the finish shows some dulling (storage wear) from the box and some freckles of surface rust on the underside matte surfaces of the gun and in the slide serrations. These should cleanm, as this is a stainless gun. Otherwise, the gun is very sharp with just a few scatterred surface marks. The Screw heads are sharp. The markings are crisp. Overall, this gun rates in about Very Good - Fine condition. 

Mechanics: The action functions well, though we have not test fired this gun. 

Box & Accessories: The gun comes with its original box, but no paperwork. One 8-Round Colt magazine is included. 

Our Assessment: The Colt Double Eagle is a double-action / single action, semi-automatic pistol manufactured by Colt's Manufacturing Company between 1989 and 1997. The design of the Double Eagle was based on the Colt M1911 pistol. Magazines are single stack and are identical to magazines shipped with the 1911. Most of the Double Eagle models were available in stainless steel only. The slide used a version of Colt's series 80 locking firing pin safety, but unlike Colt's series 80 pistols, the Double Eagle Officer's model in .45 ACP held an 8 round magazine. Here is finally your chance to stick with an American Double Action Semi Auto Pistol

title: Want To Buy:  concealable .357
postcontent:
I want a concealable .357 magnum. Rugers and Smiths, stainless steel preferred. I have around 400 to throw around.

I know I'm not going to get a response to this post. Or if I do, it will be some guy trying to get my first born for his gun. $650 for a used ruger sp101? $450 for a used LCR? $400 + for a POS rossi or beat up tuarus? And this isnt just revolvers...$450 used sig p2022's, $500 + for used glocks? And rifles too...$400 + used sks's, $6-700 used WASR AK's, lots of $400 AK's with a quadrail marked up to $600 +? Old beat up suplus rifles for $400 +....I'm guessing not too many posters make it out to gunshops these days, cause I can get half this crap from a dealer for a good $50-100 bucks less...BRAND NEW.

Some of these posts are downright comical...or criminal, whichever you look at it. I constantly flag posts for being over priced, but its not enough. I've been watching armslist decline for two years now. I think I've had enough of dealing with people that either want too damn much for their piece, or dealing with guys who will cut your legs out from under you to get your bottom dollar on an honest deal. Any decent moderation here has long since gone to hell, as I recognize posts from the same shady characters I've dealt with, over and over. Just seems worse as time goes on. Armslist is a great idea, but as with all good things, people just plain suck. And they will bring it down with them.

I'm positive any replies I get will be those I'm talking about, and I dont really give a damn. This will probably be the last post ever from me. I'd rather go through all the paperwork than keep getting screwed.

If you DO have what I'm looking for, and for a fair price, please let me know, and I'll be more than happy to do business with you. Thank you.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Spanish FR-8 Mauser
location: Southeast Wake County, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Very nice Spanish Mauser FR-8 in .308 caliber! These guns were reworked from M.1943 Mauser rifles, and this one is accordingly stamped on the receiver, "Fabrica De Armas La Coruna 1955". The receiver displays a slightly fading Spanish crest. FR-8 was used for practice by Spanish soldiers before they were issued CETME assault rifles. The rifle has a fake gas tube installed under the barrel, to make it look like the CETME rifle. This fake gas tube is actually a cleaning kit container (the cleaning kit is not included). This gun has stronger, 1898-type action than FR-7, which was build on 1893-type action. Straight bolt handle. Stock with pistol grip. The stock does not display any markings. All matching serial numbers (the matching serial numbers are stamped on the receiver, barrel and on the bolt only; all the remaining parts do not display any numbers, which is correct for this model). CONDITION: Excellent, as rebuilt by Spanish arsenal. Most of phosphate finish is still on metal. Very nice stock has been filled in one place. Excellent bore with strong and shiny rifling. Strong action. All the internal parts of the rifle are in excellent condition, with little visible wear. Mechanically, the rifle is in great condition.

Trade Interests:
Ruger LCR
SKS
Pocket Guns
Beater AK or Saiga

This is an 8 shot Iver Johnson Model 55 .22. It's an old but good one. It was manufactured sometime between 1961 and 1978. The action is still very crisp. A good part of the bluing on the barrel has turned to patina and it has plenty of wear all over pistol.  The grips feel good in the hand but are plastic, not wood as the picture may suggest. This gun would be perfect for a tackle box, tool box, boat storage etc. It is nothing special, but it goes bang every time you pull the trigger, and if it gets scratched, beat up, or otherwise miss treated you don't have to get sick over it.
As with any gun in this condition and this old it is not 100% the pull pin cylinder release will no longer come out, fortunately there is a loading gate on the right side and a twig or other small rod like tool can be used to push the spent shells out the loading gate however, the cylinder still rotates freely so the CRITICAL functions of the gun are not impaired.  I am not partial to this firearm so please don't hesitate to make an offer, at the same time I'm not going to give it away for a song and dance..
